						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of the village <hi rend="italic">chāvaḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>1651 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1573, Khara, Chaitra ba. 5, corresponding to 1651 A.D., March 31. The weekday is not mentioned.</p>						

						<p>It records a <hi rend="italic">kowl</hi> granted by the Muslim officer of Kalikere-sīme exempting tax on the construction of new houses for a period of seven years. The details are not clear.</p>						

						</summary>
